Package com.ezasm.parsing

Class Line

java.lang.Object
com.ezasm.parsing.Line
public class Line extends Object
The tokenized representation of a line. Consists of: one instruction token representing the instruction, one register token representing where the result of the operation will be stored, and any number of "right-hand side" tokens (e.g. any tokens which can represent a value).

      Creates and validates a line based on the given tokens.
      Parameters:
      instruction - the String representing the instruction.
      storeRegister - the String representing the register to store into for this operation.
      arguments - the variable sized arguments token String list.
      Throws:
      ParseException - if any of the given String tokens cannot be parsed into their corresponding types.
